-- BHP Billiton, James Hardie, Newcrest Mining, Rio: Australian Stock Preview
-- B y   S h a n i   R a j a
-- 2010-11-15T21:18:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/bhp-billiton-james-hardie-newcrest-mining-australian-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may rise or fall in Australia. This preview
includes news announced after markets closed. All prices are
from yesterday’s close unless otherwise stated.  The S&P/ASX 200 Index  futures contract  due in December
added 0.2 percent to 4,714 as of 7:47 a.m. in Sydney. The  Bank
of New York Australia ADR Index  gained 1 percent. The  S&P/ASX
200 Index  dipped 0.1 percent to 4,688.  Mining shares: Copper futures for March delivery rose 0.7
percent to close at $3.9245 a pound at 1:39 p.m. in New York as
sales at U.S. retailers climbed the most in seven months,
bolstering optimism for the economy  BHP Billiton Ltd.  (BHP AU), the world’s largest mining
company, lost 0.4 percent to A$44.14 in Sydney. Its American
depositary receipts climbed 0.9 percent in New York trading.  BHP may raise its dividend in the first half after
scrapping a $40 billion takeover bid for Potash Corp. of
Saskatchewan Inc., Goldman Sachs & Partners Australia Pty said.
Separately, BHP was reinitiated with a “conviction buy”
recommendation at Goldman Sachs Group Inc.  Rio Tinto Group  (RIO AU), the world’s third-biggest miner,
advanced 0.2 percent to A$87.04 in Sydney.  Gold producers: Gold futures for December delivery rose 0.8
percent to $1,375.80 at 12:05 p.m. in New York on bets that
mounting sovereign debt will erode currencies and boost demand
for the precious metal as an alternative asset.  Newcrest Mining Ltd.  (NCM AU), Australia’s biggest gold
producer, fell 2 percent to A$41.66.  James Hardie Industries SE  (JHX AU): The biggest seller of
home siding in the U.S. was downgraded to “underperform” from
“neutral” at Credit Suisse Group AG. The stock was unchanged
at A$5.65.  To contact the reporter for this story:
 Shani Raja  in Sydney at 
 sraja4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 